  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dd6.\u0d91\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Reduce the number of people in the UN session",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Due to the resurgence of the Covid disease in New York City, the United Nations has informed its 193 member states to limit the number of delegates participating in the 77th session of the United Nations General Assembly starting on September 20 to between 3 and 5.",
        "The United Nations stated that the number of delegates should be between 3 and 5, especially in the United Nations headquarters and when political leaders meet and discuss face to face.",
        "Sunday Times pointed out that the most important question is whether the president, the foreign minister or the ambassador will represent Sri Lanka in the 77th session of the United Nations General Assembly.",
        "The Sunday Times newspaper reported that usually 132 delegates from Sri Lanka participate in a United Nations General Assembly session.",
        "Most of them participate as representatives in order to take a vacation with the public's tax money and they spend time visiting tourist attractions, buying goods with discounts from Sri Lankan businessmen in America and spending time whitewashing or visiting their relatives and friends in America. The Sunday Times pointed out.",
        "The newspaper also stated that if Sri Lanka decided to have a large group of delegates participate this year as well, it is not possible to tell how many of those delegations requested political asylum from the United States of America."
      ],
